Quote: Last Anzac Day in Wellington the bells of the refurbished National War Memorial Carillon sounded for the fallen... Carillons (generally pronounced here as if spelt "carillion") consist of at least 23 stationary bells, which sound when struck by clappers controlled by wires attached to a clavier (keyboard).
